input: The cow eats the lion. The cow eats the mouse. The cow likes the lion. The cow does not visit the mouse. The cow visits the rabbit. The lion is not rough. The lion visits the mouse. universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Cow : obj
constant Lion : obj
constant Mouse : obj
constant Rabbit : obj

constant Eats : obj → obj → Prop
constant Likes : obj → obj → Prop
constant Visits : obj → obj → Prop
constant Rough : obj → Prop
constant Round : obj → Prop
constant Kind : obj → Prop
constant Big : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Eats Cow Lion
axiom T2 : Eats Cow Mouse
axiom T3 : Likes Cow Lion
axiom T4 : ¬ Visits Cow Mouse
axiom T5 : Visits Cow Rabbit
axiom T6 : ¬ Rough Lion
axiom T7 : Visits Lion Mouse
axiom T8 : Eats Mouse Rabbit
axiom T9 : Visits Mouse Lion
axiom T10 : Eats Rabbit Lion

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Kind x → Big x
axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, Round x → Eats x Lion
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Eats x Mouse ∧ Visits Mouse Lion → Round x
axiom R4 : Likes Cow Lion ∧ Visits Cow Lion → Visits Cow Rabbit
axiom R5 : Likes Lion Cow → ¬ Eats Lion Rabbit
axiom R6 : Eats Mouse Lion → ¬ Eats Mouse Cow
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Likes x Lion → Eats Lion Mouse
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Visits x Cow ∧ Likes x Lion → ¬ Eats Lion Mouse
axiom R9 : ∀ x : obj, Eats x Lion → Likes x Cow

theorem lion_does_not_eat_rabbit : ¬ Eats Lion Rabbit :=
begin
  apply R5,
  apply R9,
  exact T1,
end

-- The answer is True
